| What is a Function (Method)? |
================================
👉 A method is a block of code that performs a specific task. It runs only when it is called. Methods improve code 
   reusability, readability, and modularity.

👉 Performs a specific task.
👉 Runs only when called.
👉 Reduces code duplication.
👉 Improves readability.
👉 Improves code reusability.
👉 Makes programs modular.
👉 Can accept parameters.
👉 Can return a value.

