👉 Access Modifier -> An access modifier determines where a method can be accessed from.
_________________________________________
| Modifier  | Accessible From           |
| --------- | ------------------------- |
| public    | Anywhere                  |
| private   | Same class only           |
| protected | Same package + subclasses |
| default   | Same package              |
-----------------------------------------

👉 static Keyword -> The static keyword means the method belongs to the class rather than an object.
👉 Return Type -> The return type specifies what value a method returns after execution.
👉 Method Name -> The method name is the identifier used to call the method.
  👉 Should begin with a letter, _, or $.
  👉 Cannot start with a number.
  👉 Cannot be a Java keyword.
  👉 Use camelCase naming convention.
👉 Parameters -> Parameters are variables that receive values when a method is called.
👉 Method Body -> The method body contains the statements that define what the method does.

