  }

Key Points
-----------
👉 public → Method can be accessed from anywhere.
👉 static → Method belongs to the class.
👉 void → No value is returned.
👉 welcome → Method name.
👉 () → Parameters (currently empty).
👉 {} → Method body.

==========================
| Method Calling in Java |
==========================
👉 Method calling is the process of invoking a method so that its code executes. methodName();
  👉 A method executes only when it is called.
  👉 A method can be called multiple times.
  👉 Control transfers to the called method.
  👉 After execution, control returns to the calling method.

----------------------------------------------- // Simple Method Call
public class Main {
    public static void hello() {
        System.out.println("Hello Java");
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        hello();   
    }
}

Program Starts
       │
       ▼
main() starts
       │
       ▼
hello();
       │
       ▼
hello() executes
       │
       ▼
Prints:
Hello Java
       │
       ▼
Returns to main()
       │
       ▼
Program Ends
------------------------------------------------  // Calling a Method Multiple Times
public class Main {                      
    public static void hello() {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        hello();   
        hello();
        hello();
    }
}
------------------------------------------------- // Calling Different Methods
public class Main {
    public static void welcome() {
        System.out.println("Welcome");
    }

    public static void bye() {
        System.out.println("Good Bye");
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        welcome();    
        bye();
    }
}
--------------------------------------------------- // One Method Calling Another
public class Main {

    public static void message() {
        System.out.println("Have a Nice Day");
    }

    public static void welcome() {
        System.out.println("Welcome");
        message();
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        welcome();    
    }
}
---------------------------------------------------- // Nested Method Calls
public class Main {

    public static void first() {
        System.out.println("First");
        second();
    }

    public static void second() {
        System.out.println("Second");
        third();
    }

    public static void third() {
        System.out.println("Third");
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        first();    
    }
}

=====================
| Method Parameters |
=====================
👉 Parameters are variables declared in a method definition that receive values when the method is called.
  👉 Parameters receive data from the caller.
  👉 They are declared inside the parentheses ().
  👉 A method can have zero, one, or multiple parameters.
  👉 Parameters are local to the method.
  👉 The values passed during the method call are called arguments.

